ce:section.ce:para:
For EL, 0.5-cm diameter discs of fully expanded fresh leaves were washed three times with deionized water. The leaf discs were incubated at room temperate (24 h) and then the initial electrical conductivity (EC1) was recorded by a conductivity meter (Hanna, HI98192). Later, the samples were incubated in a water bath (95 °C, 20 min) for releasing all electrolytes and then were cooled down (25 °C) and the final electrical conductivity (EC2) was measured (Nayyar, 2003). The electrolyte leakage (EL) was calculated from following equation;

                              100
                              EL (%) = (EC1/EC2) ×
